  "time_ut": 1661210062,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dab \u0d85\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0da2\u0d82\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The weather forecast was wrong and there was a scandal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In Hungary, the heads of the National Meteorological Service have been immediately dismissed from their posts for issuing incorrect weather forecasts.",
        "Last Saturday (20), Hungarians prepared to celebrate St. Stephen's Day. St. Stephen's Day is considered a national holiday, and a spectacular fireworks display is held that night.",
        "The state-sponsored, annual fireworks display is one of Hungary's hallmarks, with more than 20 million people flocking to the capital city of Budapest to witness it.",
        "On the 20th, 40,000 flowers were prepared at 240 locations along the Danube River in a distance of 5 kilometers in the capital of Budapest, with the aim of lighting them at night.",
        "As everything was getting ready for the fireworks display, the Hungarian National Meteorological Service issued forecasts indicating that a violent rainstorm would hit the city and that the fireworks display would not be possible. Accordingly, the fireworks display was reluctantly cancelled. This caused many people to be unhappy.",
        "However, belying the forecast, the rain storm bypassed the capital and the capital was said not to have received any rain. The Hungarian media also reported that it rained only in a few areas in the east.",
        "Protests and displeasure arose among the Hungarian people that the National Meteorological Service could not make accurate weather forecasts. The heads of the National Meteorological Service apologized to the public on social media, but the Minister of Innovation, Laszlo Palkowicz, moved to remove the heads from their positions."
      ],
